167 The funds appropriated for Workforce Development are to be expended for those costs
168 incurred by the State in honoring commitments to pay workforce development costs,
169 including services and other assistance and expenses of recruitment and training of
170 a company's workforce, that are undertaken to induce companies to locate and expand
171 their operations in Alabama (described hereinafter as a "Project") and to develop
172 and implement training, placement and recruitment programs that will improve
173 development and expand the State's workforce. Such costs include, but are not
174 limited to: (i) AIDT operating costs directly related to a Project; (ii) wages and
175 benefits for trainers engaged by AIDT for the purpose of a Project; (iii) costs
176 which the State has agreed to pay under the terms of a Project Agreement with a
177 company that are necessary and reasonable charges incurred by the company or its
178 affiliates for personnel providing training to the company's employees, whether
179 those trainers are employees of the company or its vendors or suppliers, including
180 wages, benefits and travel (domestic and, when necessary, international); (iv) any
181 necessary materials, equipment, manuals, or other relevant training materials; (v)
182 the costs incurred for purchasing or repairing or replacing training tools and
183 equipment; (vi) costs incurred for the purchase or construction and maintenance of
184 training facilities; (vii) travel expenses for prospective and current employees and
185 trainees, including travel, food, lodging, relocation, and other costs necessary and
186 reasonable to enable the company to secure a qualified workforce; and (viii) outside
187 training fees. The above funds appropriated for Workforce Development shall be
188 expended primarily for the training of Alabama residents. It is further the intent
189 that contracts with vendors to provide workforce training shall be inclusive and
190 reflect the racial and gender diversity of the State. The Secretary of the
191 Department of Commerce shall report semi-annually to the Chairs of the Senate
192 Committee on Finance and Taxation-Education, the House Ways and Means-Education
193 Committee, the Finance Director, and the Legislative Fiscal Officer any funds
194 allocated for workforce training. Such report shall include a summary of the persons
195 trained and the vendors providing the training. The report shall contain information
196 including the residence, race and gender of the persons trained and of the principal
197 or majority owner of the firm or business contracted with to provide the training
198 services.
