332 Scholarship Program
333 The Board of Trustees of the Alabama Community College System, in consultation
334 with the Alabama Industrial Development and Training Institute, shall
335 establish qualifications for the award of scholarships to high school students
336 and adults enrolled in a state educational program relating to the automotive
337 manufacturing industry and shall further provide for the implementation and
338 administration of the scholarships. Scholarship recipients shall be selected
339 by the Board, in consultation with a scholarship committee, comprised of
340 members of the Board of Directors of the Alabama Automotive Manufacturers
341 Association, from applications submitted to the association. The Board shall
342 file a report with the Chairs of the Senate Committee on Finance and
343 Taxation-Education, the House Ways and Means-Education Committee, the
344 Legislative Fiscal Officer, and the Finance Director on September 30, 2027
345 regarding the total number of scholarships awarded for the Fall term of the
346 2026-2027 academic year and the institution attended by the scholarship
347 recipients. The report shall also include the name of each scholarship
348 recipient and the number of years the recipient has received a scholarship.
