993 The above appropriation includes funds to pay salary supplements and related benefit costs for
994 Certified Academic Language Therapists (CALT) and other costs of the program. Supplement
995 amounts will be determined by the availability of funds based on the number of CALT
996 Teachers. The state of Alabama will provide an annual supplement of $5,000 to any CALT that is
997 employed full-time in a public K-12 school system or public independent school and is properly
998 certified by the state of Alabama. The existing eligibility criteria will apply: (a) CALTs
999 employed on less than a full-time contract on October 1 will receive a pro-rata share of the
1000 salary supplement. (b) CALTs employed full-time after October 1 will receive a pro-rata share
1001 of the salary supplement. (c) Any CALT employed full-time in Alabama and properly certified by
1002 the state of Alabama will receive the annual salary stipend. (d) CALTs employed as a substitute
1003 are not eligible for the salary supplement. (e) CALTs who are on leave of absence for more than
1004 half a school year will receive a prorated amount based on the number of months worked during
1005 the school year. (f) CALTs will receive the salary supplement each year of the valid period of
1006 the CALT credentials unless the Alabama Legislature declines to make the annual appropriation.
1007 (g) CALTs must maintain their CALT credentials in order to continue receiving the salary
1008 supplement. (h) CALTs employed in the final year of their CALT credentials valid period will
1009 receive a prorated amount based on the number of months worked covered in that valid period.
1010 (i) CALTs who leave after October 1 will be eligible for a prorated amount based on the months
