1015 Of the above appropriation, $17,200,000 shall be expended for the Alabama Summer and
1016 Afterschool Program (ASAP) grants program with the objective of reducing the achievement gap in
1017 students who are not proficient in reading and/or math.
1018 The State Superintendent of Education shall administer the grants process. Grants shall be
1019 awarded to a) local education agencies, municipalities, and not-for-profit organizations for
1020 summer and afterschool programs that provide direct services and b) to entities that provide
1021 support to summer and after-school programs. Afterschool programs shall be guided by the
1022 Alabama Afterschool Quality Standards; summer programs shall be guided by the "Final Report and
1023 Recommendations" of the Alabama Campaign for Grade-Level Reading, Pages 81-92.
1024 Data on student and program outcomes shall be collected and used to inform a continuous
1025 improvement process. A report shall be provided to the Legislature listing grantees and
1026 summarizing outcomes.
1027 The intent of the Legislature is to increase access to evidence-based, high-quality summer and
1028 afterschool programming, to build a diverse delivery model of providers, and to foster
1029 collaboration between local education agencies and community-based organizations. The goal is
1030 to award at least 60% of the funding to nonprofit, community based organizations or
1031 partnerships between community-based organizations and local education agencies.
