1368 The above appropriation includes funds to pay salary supplements and related benefit costs for
1369 Nationally Board-Certified Teachers (NBCT) and other costs of the program. Supplement amounts
1370 will be determined by the availability of funds based on the number of National Board Certified
1371 Teachers. (1) The state of Alabama will provide an annual supplement of $5,000 to any NBCT that
1372 is employed full-time in a public K-12 school and is properly certified by the state of
1373 Alabama. The existing eligibility criteria will apply: (a) NBCTs employed on a less than
1374 full-time contract on October 1 will receive a pro-rata share of the salary supplement. (b)
1375 NBCTs employed full-time after October 1 will receive a pro-rata share of the salary
1376 supplement. (c) NBCTs who earn National Board Certification in another state and are teaching
1377 full-time in Alabama on October 1 and are properly certified by the state of Alabama will
1378 receive the annual salary stipend. (d) NBCTs employed as a substitute are not eligible for the
1379 salary supplement. (e) NBCTs who are on leave of absence for more than half a school year will
1380 receive a prorated amount based on the number of months worked during the school year. (f)
1381 NBCTs will receive the salary supplement each year of the valid period of the certificate
1382 unless the Alabama Legislature declines to make the annual appropriation. (g) NBCTs must renew
1383 their certificate by the year of the certificate's expiration in order to continue receiving
1384 the salary supplement. (h) NBCTs employed in the final year of the certificate valid period
1385 will receive a prorated amount based on the number of months worked covered in that valid
1386 period. (i) NBCTs who leave after October 1 will be eligible for a prorated amount based on the
1387 months served. (j) NBCTs must remain employed with a public K-12 local Board of Education in
1388 order to continue receiving the salary supplement. (2) In addition to the supplement provided
1389 by subsection (1) of this section, classroom teachers shall be eligible for an additional
1390 supplement of $5,000 if in an instructional assignment in challenging, high poverty schools,
