1958 The Board in determining those areas in greatest need of medical service shall
1959 primarily be guided by information, on the rural primary care service areas
1960 that have a deficit of primary-care physicians, provided by the most recent
1961 Status Report of the Alabama Primary Care Physician Workforce from the Office
1962 for Family Health Education & Research at the UAB Huntsville Regional Medical
1963 Campus. Other factors used by the Board in determining areas of greatest need
1964 shall include the practice locations agreed to by people granted loans
1965 beforehand by the Board but who have not yet started clinical practice, or
1966 started practice too late to have been included in the most recent Status
1967 Report. The Board shall give preference to physicians that reside in the area
1968 of greatest need. The Board shall file a report with the Chair of the Senate
1969 Committee on Finance and Taxation-Education, the Chair of the House Ways and
1970 Means-Education Committee, the Legislative Fiscal Officer and the Finance
1971 Director on October 1, 2026. The Board’s report shall include, if determined,
1972 where each student who has not started clinical practice has contracted to
1973 practice clinical medicine to repay his or her loans. If that area is not a
1974 rural primary-care service area identified as having a deficit of primary-care
1975 physicians by the most recent Status Report of the Alabama Primary Care
1976 Physician Workforce, the Board in its report shall state why it allowed that
1977 location as a place where that student could practice to repay his or her
1978 loans. The report shall also include the total number of scholarships awarded
1979 for the fall term of the 2025-2026 academic year and the institution attended
1980 by the scholarship recipients. The report shall also include the name of each
1981 scholarship recipient and the number of years the recipient has received a
1982 scholarship and, if determined, where the recipient has contracted to practice
1983 clinical medicine to repay his or her loans. The report shall also report
1984 where contract holders were working in clinical practice to repay their loans,
1985 how many in each location, where physicians who had repaid their loans worked
1986 to do so, and how many in each location. The report also shall detail the
1987 Board’s budget and operating expenses for the 2025-2026 fiscal year.
