2593 Section 4. Any state agency, local board of education,
2594 or public institution of higher education receiving funding
2595 from the Education Trust Fund in this appropriations act shall
2596 be in compliance with the provisions of Act 2024-34 of the
2597 2024 Regular Session of the Legislature.
2598 Section 5. In addition to the appropriations herein
2599 made, all gifts, grants, contributions, insurance proceeds or
2600 entitlements, in excess of the amount carried in this act,
2601 including grants by the Congress of the United States,
2602 municipalities or counties, to any department, division,
2603 board, bureau, commission, agency, institution, office or
2604 officer of the State of Alabama are hereby appropriated and,
2605 in the event the same are recurring, are reappropriated to
2606 such department, division, board, bureau, commission, agency,
2607 institution, office, or officer to be used only for the
2608 purpose or purposes for which the grant or contribution was or
2609 shall be made. Further, all state, county, municipal, and
2610 educational entities are authorized to disburse such sums as
2611 deemed necessary by mutual agreement between said entities and
2612 the State of Alabama, Department of Examiners of Public
2613 Accounts to partially defray the cost of auditing services
2614 performed by said agency. All such sums are hereby
2615 appropriated and reappropriated if necessary to the Department
Page 97

appropriated and reappropriated if necessary to the Department
SB141 INTRODUCED
2616 of Examiners of Public Accounts for audit services, to be
2617 expended through the fund established by Section 41-5A-22,
2618 Code of Alabama 1975.
2619 Section 6. The State Superintendent of Education shall
2620 make requisitions to the State Comptroller in favor of the
2621 proper beneficiary in accordance with the law and rules and
2622 regulations governing the expenditure or disbursement of any
2623 and all funds appropriated to the State Department of
2624 Education and/or the State Board of Education in this act,
2625 whereupon the Comptroller shall issue her warrant therefor.
2626 All other appropriations in this act shall be paid after
2627 proper requisitions are made to the State Comptroller in the
2628 manner now provided by law.
2629 Section 7. Nothing in this act shall be construed to
2630 affect or repeal any law authorizing or permitting any
2631 college, school, or other education or eleemosynary
2632 institution of the State to receive, collect or disburse any
2633 fees, tuitions, charges, sales, endowments, trusts or income
2634 therefrom, which are now or may hereafter be authorized to
2635 receive, collect, or disburse. The receiving college, school
2636 or institution shall further maintain separate accounts for
2637 such receipts or shall maintain a system of accounting which
2638 will show a cash flow of such receipts received under the
2639 provision of this appropriation.
2640 Section 8. The appropriations made herein to the
2641 departments, boards, offices, commissions, and agencies
2642 include the amounts necessary and said departments, boards,
