2650 manner for such services.
2651 Section 9. All encumbered balances of a previous
2652 fiscal year appropriation other than the exclusions authorized
2653 by the Code of Alabama 1975, Section 41-4-93, shall lapse no
2654 later than September 30 of the fiscal year immediately
2655 following the fiscal year for which the appropriation was made
2656 and shall revert to the credit of the Education Trust Fund or
2657 earmarked fund from which the appropriation or appropriations
2658 were made.
2659 Section 10. Upon certification to the Director of
2660 Finance by the State Attorney General that a federal court has
2661 ordered the State of Alabama to pay claims, attorney fees, or
2662 other costs relating to said court order, funds are hereby
2663 appropriated to the affected department, board, bureau, or
2664 commission in the amount necessary to satisfy that court
2665 order. Such appropriations are in addition to any other
2666 appropriation heretofore or hereafter made in this
2667 appropriation act. Such appropriations are conditioned upon
2668 the availability of funds and a determination by the Director
2669 of Finance that other current appropriations are not available
