2670 for court-ordered payments.
2671 Section 11. Local boards of education may exercise
2672 flexibility among line item expenditures, not to create a
2673 reduction of earned teacher units and/or local board of
2674 education support personnel.
2675 Section 12. The State Superintendent of Education may
2676 approve a request by a local board of education for
2677 redirecting Other Current Expense funds designated for
2678 pass-through calculations to their local Child Nutrition
2679 Program if the redirected funds do not prevent the Child
2680 Nutrition Program of that local board of education from
2681 maintaining a one-month fund balance.
2682 Section 13. The appropriations made herein to the
2683 departments, boards, offices, commissions, and agencies
2684 include the amounts necessary to pay the State Employees'
2685 Insurance Board (SEIB). The SEIB rate shall be $1,175 per
2686 month for each full-time employee for the fiscal year ending
2687 September 30, 2027. The State Employees' Insurance Board will
2688 adjust the insurance program wherever appropriate to maintain
2689 the aforementioned fixed rate.
2690 Section 14. Notwithstanding any other provisions of
2691 this act or any other act, any amount from appropriations for
2692 the fiscal year ending September 30, 2026 to the various state
2693 agencies and institutions in this act, including
2694 appropriations from the Education Trust Fund, which are
2695 unexpended and reverted on September 30, 2026 are hereby
2696 reappropriated to the respective state agencies, offices, and
