2697 institutions for the fiscal year beginning October 1, 2026.
2698 Section 15. The At-Risk and High Hopes appropriations
2699 made to the State Department of Education shall be expended at
2700 the discretion of the State Superintendent of Education, with
2701 input from other Alabama State Department of Education
2702 advisory personnel, for activities or programs designed to
2703 enhance outcomes for At-Risk Students. In an effort to provide
2704 the best and most efficient implementation, administration of
2705 the funds shall be assigned to and allocated by the Alabama
2706 State Department of Education's Division of Administrative and
2707 Financial Support.
2708 Section 16. (a) All nongovernmental entities,
2709 identified by the Legislative Services Agency, which are
2710 allocated funds in Section 3 of this act shall file a report
2711 with the Chairs of the House Ways and Means-Education
2712 Committee, the Senate Committee on Finance and
2713 Taxation-Education, Finance Director, and the Legislative
2714 Fiscal Officer prior to the start of the 2027 Regular Session,
2715 regarding the proposed expenditures and usage of the funds
2716 appropriated in the fiscal year ending September 30, 2027. The
2717 Legislative Services Agency shall provide notice to the
2718 identified nongovernmental entities within 60 days following
2719 enactment of this act regarding the reporting requirements and
2720 the methodology to submit reports and format to be used, which
2721 may include an online platform.
